notes: ::taxonomy:Strain BN/SsNHsd/Mcwi::endTaxonomy:"The BN rat was selected as a sequencing target by the research  community. An inbred animal (BN/SsNHsd) was obtained by  the Medical College of Wisconsin (MCW) from Harlan Sprague  Dawley. Most of the sequence data  were from two females, with a small amount of whole genome  shotgun (WGS) and ﬂow-sorted Y chromosome sequencing from  a male. The Y chromosome is not included in the current  assembly." Only info provided for mtDNA is that "variant A' was sequenced. The actual sequence could not be found in Genbank so one produced a year later by the Baylor Inst. was used (no publication provided) (Gibbs et al. Genome sequence of the Brown  Norway rat yields insights into  mammalian evolution. Nature. 428: 493-521) (Gadaleta et al.
